{"000-section": {"000-title": "Telangana 100% Input Subsidy Scheme For Backward Castes (BC) of Upto Rs. 1 Lakh"}, "001-section": {"000-title": "Telangana 100% Input Subsidy Scheme for Backward Castes (BC)", "001-normal": "The highlights and important features of this investment support scheme are as follows:-", "002-listElement": "- Telangana govt. has announced a scheme where each BC beneficiary will get 100% input subsidy up to Rs 1 lakh.", "003-listElement": "- The new scheme is for poor people of around 100 castes in BCs who requires investment support.", "004-listElement": "- Barbers, Blacksmiths, Goldsmiths, Potters, Masons, and other small traders from BC community like vegetable vendors and flower businessmen will benefit.", "005-listElement": "- In the first phase, there would be no bank linkage.", "006-listElement": "- Financial assistance will be given to all those people who are in their hereditary professions and small trades from backward castes (BC Category).", "007-listElement": "- These people indulged in hereditary business can purchase tools with this input subsidy.", "008-listElement": "- For the major castes in BCs, the state govt. has been already implementing schemes like sheep rearing for Yadavas and Gollas, washing machines for the washermen caste and schemes for fishermen.", "009-normal": "Previously, govt. has launched a similar Input Subsidy Scheme to provide investment support to farmers named as [Rythu Bandhu Scheme](https://sarkariyojana.com/rythu-bandhu-scheme-telangana-farmers-investment-support-scheme-fiss/). First phase of Rythu Bandhu Scheme is already ongoing and second phase is expected to be implemented from October 2018."}, "002-section": {"000-title": "Telangana 100% Input Subsidy Scheme \u2013 Investment Support Implementation", "001-normal": "Govt. will identify all the beneficiaries at the village level. Govt. will form committees in every district with collector as chairman, BC welfare officer as convenor and joint collector as members. After preparing the List of beneficiaries, govt. will provide financial assistance to all such beneficiaries.", "002-normal": "All the people in the Beneficiary List must possess a valid Bank Account as this assistance amount will be transferred directly to their bank accounts. Govt. will provide funds allocated to the BC welfare department and MBC Corporation for this purpose."}}